LANDING_PAGE_SUB_HERO_TEXT: Design and create unique rings imbued with ancient magic. Become a legendary ringsmith.
FEATURE_1_BODY: Harness the fires of Mount Doom to forge the One Ring to Rule Them All. Imbue it with your dark will to dominate Middle-earth.
FEATURE_2_BODY: Forge rings of power for the Elven realms using ancient Elvish magic and craft. Each one amplifies the natural abilities of its bearer.
FEATURE_3_BODY: Created in the fiery forges of the Dwarven kingdoms, these rings grant mastery over mining and metalworking to their wielders.
FEATURE_4_BODY: Call upon foul sorceries passed down by the darkest of Maiar to bind powerful spells into your forged rings of power.
FEATURE_5_BODY: Craft the rings in utmost secrecy and offer them as gifts to unwitting kings, lords and rulers to bring them under your thrall.
FEATURE_6_BODY: Once the rings are dispersed, exert your will through them to conquer the realms of Elves, Dwarves and Men under one rule.

PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions About Ring Crafting
ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: What materials are needed to make the Rings?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: To forge the powerful Rings, you'll need rare metals mined from the depths of the earth - mithril, gold, and forge-fired titanium. Ancient elvish craft and dwarven smithing skills are also essential.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: How long does it take to make a Ring?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Crafting a single Ring of Power is an arduous process that can take many months or even years of meticulous work by a team of skilled craftsmen. Patience and perseverance are vital.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What special abilities do the Rings possess?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: The Rings grant their bearers command over the elements and dominion over the wills of others. However, their full powers are still shrouded in mystery and legend.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Is it safe to wield a Ring of Power?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Wielding the Rings carries great peril, for they are tied to the fate of Middle-earth itself. Only those of purest heart and strongest will can resist their corrupting influence.
CTA_BODY: In the fires of Mount Doom, where the shadows lie, forge a master Ring to rule them all and bind them.
FAQ_TITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Forging the One Ring: Your Questions Answered
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get insights into the making of the powerful artifact
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_1: What is the One Ring made of?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: The One Ring was forged from pure and utterly corrupted Morgul-metal in the fires of Mount Doom by the Dark Lord Sauron.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: Sauron poured his cruelty, malice and will to dominate all life into the molten metal, giving the Ring its immense power of control over the other Rings of Power.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What powers does the Ring possess?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: The One Ring has the ability to control the other Rings and their bearers. It amplifies the natural desires of its bearer, eventually corrupting them utterly. It can also help extend the bearer's life span.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Why was the Ring so difficult to destroy?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: The Ring was virtually indestructible, except in the fiery pits of Mount Doom where it was originally forged. Part of Sauron's life force bound to the Ring protected it from normal means of damage.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: How was the Ring eventually unmade?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: After an epic journey, Frodo Baggins took the Ring to the volcanic Mount Doom and cast it back into the fiery chasm from whence it came, finally destroying Sauron's dread artifact once and for all.
